'''Felice Nicole Herrig''' (born September 18, 1984) is an American [[kickboxing|kickboxer]], [[Muay Thai|Muay Thai fighter]], and [[Mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]]. Born in [[Buffalo Grove, Illinois]], she began her career practicing kickboxing and Muay Thai before transitioning to MMA in 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Buffalo Grove fighter Felice Herrig gets her shot on reality TV|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2009-07-03/news/0907010509_1_mixed-martial-arts-fighters-mma|first=Mike|last=Helfgot|date=2009-07-03|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|accessdate=2011-10-11}}</ref> In September 2011, she signed a multi-fight deal with XFC in Florida.<ref>{{cite news|title=XFC signs Felice Herrig to multi-fight deal|url=http://prommanow.com/index.php/2011/09/20/xfc-signs-felice-herrig-to-multi-fight-deal/|first=Jack|last=Bratcher|date=2011-09-20|work=ProMMANow.com|accessdate=2011-10-11}}</ref>

Herrig is currently the #5-ranked female strawweight fighter in the world according to the Unified Women's MMA Rankings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/rankings/unified-womens-mixed-martial-arts-rankings/|title=Unified Women's Mixed Martial Arts Rankings|publisher=MMARising.com|accessdate=2013-11-01}}</ref>

==Kickboxing career==
Prior to Felice "Lil' Bulldog" Herrig's move to Mixed Martial Arts, Herrig held a kickboxing record of 23-5/4. She is currently ranked number 2 in the World in the IKF [[International Kickboxing Federation]] Pro Women<U+2019>s Muay Thai Bantamweight Division.

As a pro kickboxer Herrig won the [[International Kickboxing Federation]] Pro Muay Thai United States Bantamweight Title. She won the title on November 15, 2008 in Chicago, Illinois, USA, when she defeated Katie Meehan by unanimous decision, 49-46, 48-47 and 49-46.

As an Amateur she was a two time [[International Kickboxing Federation]] Open Tournament Champion.

On August 21, 2005, in Orlando, Florida, USA Herrig became the 2005 IKF North American Classic Amateur Full Contact Rules Bantamweight Tournament Champion when she defeated Terri French of Little Rock, Arkansas, USA by unanimous decision 30-27 on all 3 judges cards.

On July 30, 2006 in Cedar Rapids, Iowa, USA Herring defended her IKF Tournament Title at the 2006 IKF World Classic when she defeated Stacy Chung of Thunder Bay, Ontario, Canada by unanimous decision 29-28 on all 3 judges cards.

She has also competed in the [[World Combat League]] with the St. Louis Enforcers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mouthpiecesports.com/media/mma-fighter-felice-herrig-is-bantering-with-brian-dryfhout-22562/|title=MMA Fighter Felice Herrig is Bantering with Brian Dryfhout|accessdate=2010-04-16|publisher=MouthpieceSports.com|date=2009-08-18}}</ref>

==Mixed martial arts career==
Felice appeared on [[Fight Girls]] in 2007 on the [[Oxygen Channel]] and won her fight in [[Thailand]] against a champion Thai fighter.<ref name=FIGHTHYPE>{{cite web|url=http://fighthype.com/pages/content5394.html|title=Felice Herrig: "Girls Want Nothing To Do With My Standup"|accessdate=2009-08-19|publisher=FightHype.com|date=2009-08-06}}</ref> She was later scheduled to appear on another reality show about women's MMA called the Ultimate Women Challenge.<ref name=FIGHTHYPE/>

Herrig faced Iman Achhal at UWC: Man "O" War on February 21, 2009 in her MMA debut. She lost the fight by split decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/articles/Easton-Captures-UWC-Gold-Patterson-Victorious-16298|title=Easton Captures UWC Gold; Patterson Victorious|accessdate=2010-04-16|publisher=Sherdog.com|date=2009-02-22}}</ref>

She faced Michele Gutierrez at Unconquered 1: November Reign on November 20, 2009 and won the fight by armbar submission in the second round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicagosmma.com/2009/12/highlights-of-felice-herrigs-first-mma-victory/|title=Highlights of Felice Herrig's First MMA Victory|accessdate=2010-04-16|publisher=ChicagosMMA.com|date=2009-12-03}}</ref>

Herrig faced [[Jessica Rakoczy]] at [[Bellator 14]] on April 15, 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Askren-Thomas-Cleared-for-Bellator-14-23877|title=Askren, Thomas Cleared for Bellator 14|accessdate=2010-04-16|publisher=Sherdog.com|date=2010-04-14}}</ref> She won the fight via split decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.yahoo.com/mma/blog/cagewriter/post/Herrig-ekes-out-a-split-decision-while-Curran-lo?urn=mma%2C234604|title=Herrig ekes out a split decision while Curran loses in UD at Bellator|accessdate=2010-04-16|publisher=YAHOO! Sports|date=2010-04-15}}</ref>

Herrig faced Amanda LaVoy at XFO 37 on December 4, 2010. She won the fight via armbar submission in the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultmma.com/news/index.php?itemid=1365|title=XFO 37 results <U+2013> Jeff Curran picks up win & Felice Herrig vs. Amanda LaVoy fight video |accessdate=2010-12-06|publisher=ULTMMA.com|date=2010-12-06}}</ref>

On January 14, 2011, Herrig faced [[Barb Honchak]] at Hoosier Fight Club 6: New Years Nemesis in Valparaiso, Indiana. She lost the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2011/01/15/barb-honchak-defeats-felice-herrig-at-hoosier-fight-club-6/|title=Barb Honchak Defeats Felice Herrig At Hoosier Fight Club 6|accessdate=2011-01-15|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2011-01-15}}</ref>

Herrig faced Andrea Miller at Chicago Cagefighting Championship 3 on March 5, 2011. She won the fight by TKO in the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicagosmma.com/2011/03/pulver-wins-despite-broken-foot/|title=Pulver Wins Despite Broken Foot|accessdate=2011-03-06|publisher=ChicagosMMA.com|date=2011-03-06}}</ref>

Herrig faced Nicdali Rivera-Calanoc at XFO 39 on May 13, 2011 at the Sears Centre in Hoffman Estates, Illinois. She won the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|last=MMA Recap|title=XFO 39 Results and Recap|url=http://mmarecap.com/news/XFO_39_Results_and_Recap-4281|work=MMARecap.com|publisher=MMARecap|accessdate=2011-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Felice Herrig, Amanda LaVoy Earn Victories At XFO 39|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2011/05/13/felice-herrig-amanda-lavoy-earn-victories-at-xfo-39/|first=Robert|last=Sargent|date=2011-05-13|accessdate=2011-10-11|work=MMARising.com}}</ref>

Her scheduled bout against undefeated Kelly Warren at Fight Tour on August 20, 2011 was cancelled due to Warren weighing in 7 pounds overweight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefightnerd.com/fight-tour-sylvia-vs-adams-from-rockford-il-quick-results/|title=Fight Tour: Sylvia Vs Adams from Rockford, Illinois <U+2013> Quick Results|publisher=TheFightNerd.com|accessdate=2010-08-20}}</ref>

Herrig faced [[Carla Esparza]] at [[Xtreme Fighting Championships#XFC 15: Tribute|XFC 15: Tribute]] on December 2, 2011 in Tampa, Florida.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2011/10/13/carla-esparza-vs-felice-herrig-announced-for-xfc-15/|title=Carla Esparza vs Felice Herrig Announced For XFC 15|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2011-10-13|accessdate=2011-10-19}}</ref> She was defeated by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2011/12/02/carla-esparza-defeats-felice-herrig-in-xfc-15-co-feature/|title=Carla Esparza Defeats Felice Herrig In XFC 15 Co-Feature|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2011-12-02|accessdate=2011-12-02}}</ref>

On April 13, 2012, Herrig faced Patricia Vidonic at XFC 17: Apocalypse in Jackson, Tennessee. She defeated Vidonic by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2012/04/13/felice-herrig-defeats-patricia-vidonic-at-xfc-17-apocalypse/|title=Felice Herrig Defeats Patricia Vidonic At XFC 17: "Apocalypse"|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-04-13|accessdate=2012-04-15}}</ref>

Herrig next faced Simona Soukupova at XFC 19: Charlotte Showdown on August 3, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2012/06/20/felice-herrig-vs-simona-soukupova-planned-for-xfc-19/|title=Felice Herrig vs Simona Soukupova Planned For XFC 19|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-06-20|accessdate=2012-06-22}}</ref> She defeated Soukupova by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2012/08/03/felice-herrig-defeats-simona-soukupova-in-xfc-19-co-feature/|title=Felice Herrig Defeats Simona Soukupova In XFC 19 Co-Feature|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-08-03|accessdate=2012-08-03}}</ref>

Herrig was scheduled to return to Bellator to face Michele Gutierrez in a rematch at [[Bellator_Fighting_Championships:_Season_Seven#Bellator_LXXXIV|Bellator 84]] on December 14, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2012/10/12/felice-herrig-vs-michele-gutierrez-rematch-added-to-bellator-84/|title=Felice Herrig vs Michele Gutierrez Rematch Added To Bellator 84|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-10-12|accessdate=2012-10-17}}</ref> However, Gutierrez withdrew from the fight on December 1 and Herrig instead competed in a rematch against Patricia Vidonic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2012/12/03/gutierrez-out-herrig-now-set-to-rematch-vidonic-at-bellator-84/|title=Gutierrez Out, Herrig Now Set To Rematch Vidonic At Bellator 84|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-12-03|accessdate=2012-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cagepotato.com/felice-herrig-gets-new-opponent-for-bellator-84-after-michele-gutierrez-allegedly-fakes-injury-to-cover-up-weight-issues/|title=Felice Herrig Gets New Opponent for Bellator 84 After Michele Gutierrez Allegedly Fakes Injury to Cover Up Weight Issues|publisher=CagePotato.com|date=2012-12-04|accessdate=2012-12-04}}</ref> She won the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2012/12/14/felice-herrig-defeats-patricia-vidonic-in-bellator-84-rematch/|title=Felice Herrig Defeats Patricia Vidonic In Bellator 84 Rematch|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2012-12-14|accessdate=2012-12-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmajunkie.com/news/2012/12/bellator-84-results|title=Bellator 84 results: Herrig cruises to one-sided decision in rematch|publisher=MMAjunkie.com|date=2012-12-14|accessdate=2012-12-14}}</ref>

On January 9, 2013, Herrig was signed to a one-year apparel deal with Americana MMA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-mma.tv/americana-mma-signs-bellator-hottie-felice-herrig-to-apparel-deal-examiner-com|title=Americana MMA signs Bellator hottie Felice Herrig to apparel deal|publisher=e-mmatv.com|date=2013-01-09|accessdate=2013-01-09}}</ref>

Herrig next competed against Heather Clark at [[Bellator 94]] on March 28, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2013/02/20/felice-herrig-vs-heather-clark-targeted-for-bellator-94-in-florida/|title=Felice Herrig vs Heather Clark Targeted For Bellator 94 In Florida|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2013-02-20|accessdate=2013-02-20}}</ref> She won the fight via split decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/articles/2013/03/28/jessica-aguilar-felice-herrig-victorious-at-bellator-94-in-florida/|title=Jessica Aguilar, Felice Herrig Victorious At Bellator 94 In Florida|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2013-03-28|accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref>

===Invicta Fighting Championships===
On August 13, 2013, it was announced that Herrig had signed a multi-fight deal with [[Invicta Fighting Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://invictafc.com/2013/08/felice-herrig-signs-with-invicta-fighting-championships/|title=Felice Herrig Signs With Invicta Fighting Championships|publisher=InvictaFC.com|date=2013-08-13|accessdate=2013-08-13}}</ref> She faced [[Tecia Torres]] at [[Invicta FC events#Invicta FC 7: Honchak vs. Smith|Invicta FC 7]] on December 7, 2013 and lost the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://invictafc.com/2013/10/invicta-fc-7-coming-to-kansas-city-on-december-7th/|title=INVICTA FC 7 COMING TO KANSAS CITY ON DECEMBER 7TH|publisher=InvictaFC.com|date=2013-10-11|accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2013/10/11/felice-herrig-set-to-face-tecia-torres-at-invicta-fc-7/|title=Felice Herrig Set To Face Tecia Torres At Invicta FC 7|publisher=MMARising.com|date=2013-10-11|accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>

===Ultimate Fighting Championships===
On December 11, 2013, it was announced that Herrig was signed by the UFC along with ten other strawweight fighters to compete on season 20 of The Ultimate Fighter which will crown the first ever UFC strawweight champion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmainsider.net/13572/ufc-announce-plans-for-strawweight-division-with-tuf-20-signings-of-several-invicta-fc-roster-confirmed|title=UFC Announce Plans for Strawweight Division with TUF 20, Signings of Several Invicta FC Roster Confirmed|publisher=MMAInsider.net|Author=Dave Reid|date=2013-12-11|accessdate=2013-12-11}}</ref>

